== Pickled Radish ==

Trim and thinly slice the @radish{125%grams}(thinly sliced).

Pop into a #small bowl{} along with @sugar{1%tsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and half the @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}.

Mix together and set aside. Stir frequently.

== Smashed Cucumber ==

Trim the @cucumber{1} then halve lengthways. Bash each half with the bottom of a #pot{} or pan. Thinly slice widthways.

In a separate #bowl{}, toss the smashed cucumber with the @soy sauce{1%sachet}, remaining @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet} and @sugar{1%tsp}.

Set aside, ensuring to stir occasionally.

== Bulgur ==

Place a pot over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to%taste}.

Add the @garlic, ginger & lemongrass paste{1%sachet} and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in 240ml salted @water{to%taste}(salted) and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%grams}, bring back to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pot and remove from the heat. Leave aside for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

== Teriyaki Tofu ==

Place a pan over medium heat (without oil).

Once hot, dry-fry the @sesame seeds{1%sachet} until lightly toasted, stirring regularly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the pan and set aside.

Drain the @tofu{280%grams} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Halve the @chilli{1} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Return the pan to high heat with a good glug of @oil{to%taste}.

Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, ~{6-8%minutes}. Shift frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.

Remove the pan from the heat and drain off any excess oil.

Stir in the @teriyaki sauce{1%sachet} and chilli (use less if you don't like spice).

Add a splash of @water{to%taste} to loosen the sauce. Taste and season with @salt{to%taste} and @pepper{to%taste}, if required.

== Assembly ==

Fluff up the bulgur with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{}.

Drain the pickling liquids from the radish and cucumber.

Arrange the teriyaki tofu, cucumber and radish on top of the bulgur.

Finish with a sprinkling of the toasted sesame seeds.